// T.A.R.L. policy for the governed_agent_runner example.
//
// Governed mode is fail-closed: a gated capability (write/read/import) and a
// governed-function entry are DENIED unless a wired policy returns ALLOW. This
// policy is what the example-lock runner attaches so main.thirsty can actually
// execute — governance enforced, not implied. Default deny at the bottom.

policy agent_runner

when action == "validate" => ALLOW
when action == "write" => ALLOW
when true => DENY
